# Broccoli Cheddar Chicken And Rice Casserole

Based on [https://www.halfbakedharvest.com/broccoli-cheddar-chicken-and-rice-casserole/…](https://www.halfbakedharvest.com/broccoli-cheddar-chicken-and-rice-casserole/#bo-recipe) ([wayback](http://web.archive.org/web/20251112125515/https://www.halfbakedharvest.com/broccoli-cheddar-chicken-and-rice-casserole/))

{ rating="5" image="broccoli_cheddar_chicken_and_rice_casserole.jpeg" }
:::
:::

## Ingredients

- [ ] 1 yellow onion, chopped
- [ ] 3 carrots, chopped
- [ ] 1.5 cups basmati or jasmine rice (white, brown, or blend)
- [ ] 1/2 cup dry orzo pasta (or substitute with 1 cup additional vegetables)
- [ ] 3 Tbsp salted butter
- [ ] 2 tsp dried thyme
- [ ] 1 lb boneless chicken breasts, cut into cubes
- [ ] 4 cups low sodium chicken broth
- [ ] Bag of frozen vegetables (broccoli or peas)
- [ ] 2 bay leaves
- [ ] 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- [ ] 1/2 tsp cayenne pepper, more or less to taste
- [ ] 2.5 Tbsp lemon juice
- [ ] 1/2 cup milk
- [ ] 1.5 cups shredded sharp cheddar cheese, divided (about 200g)

## Recipe

1. Prep

   1. Cut the carrots and onions and set aside
   1. In a 2 cup measure, prep the rice, orzo, butter, and thyme
1. Heat a large pot on medium heat. Saute the carrots and onions in olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and cook until fragrant (~5 min)
1. Cube the chicken and add to the pot. Add additional salt and pepper and cook until seared (~3 min)
1. Add the prepped rice, orzo, butter, and thyme. Cook until toasted (2-3 min)
1. Add the broth and bring to a boil over high heat
1. Preheat the oven to 425F
1. Add the frozen vegetable, bay leaves, garlic powder, cayenne, and more pepper. Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook for 20-25 minutes until the rice is mostly cooked
1. Stir in the lemon juice, milk, and 1/2 cup of cheese, then pour the pot into an oven-safe casserole dish. Scatter the remaining cheese over top the casserole
1. Transfer to the oven and bake 15-20 minutes, until the cheese is melted and just beginning to brown. Serve warm with additional thyme

## Notes

- **Rice options:** For lower glycemic impact, use brown basmati rice (increase cooking time to 35-40 minutes in step 7), a 50/50 brown/white rice blend (cook for 25-30 minutes), or wild rice blend
- **Flavor/texture tradeoff with brown rice:** Brown rice is chewier and has a nuttier flavor than fluffy white rice. The cheese sauce and butter help keep it creamy. Cooking time increases by 10-15 minutes. If brown rice ends up too firm, add an extra 1/4-1/2 cup broth and cook longer
- **Lower carb option:** Replace orzo with 1 cup additional chopped vegetables (mushrooms, zucchini, or cauliflower florets) to reduce carbohydrate content without sacrificing volume
- **Fiber boost:** Add 1 (15 oz) can white beans (drained and rinsed) in step 7 for extra protein and fiber
- **To Make Ahead:** Prepare the casserole and refrigerate. Let warm while pre-heating the oven and bake for 15-20 minutes as recommended
- Related to the [One-Pot Orzo with Sausage, Spinach, and Corn](../pasta/one_pot_orzo_with_sausage_spinach_and_corn.html)
